text: Guilds of Ravnica, Ravnica Allegiance announces

Hell yes. I dig that.
Battlebond. Not ravnica.
Ravnica is real blah.

It’s just never appealed to me.
Ravnica is the set that really got me in to magic
Or rather, rtr

I don’t know if it’s too much going on with all these 10 guilds and all that or what. Or that the city scape world feels like a Coruscant ripoff. I dunno. Everyone talks about ravnica being so great and I’m Just meh.
Or maybe it’s I really am over jace and rtrtr means more jace.

Guilds of Ravnica is Selesnya, Boros, Golgari, Izzet, and Dimir.
Izzet. Ohhhhh baby
Coruscant is the city planet in Star Wars that goes splodey in force awakens
Oh...I didn’t read it out loud.
Hey, they fixed partners so people can't be boring and terrible!
Meh. It’s more limited.
Encourages decks vs piles of cards
Too limited.
It’s one deck.
I shouldn't say fixed, if that's someone's jam then fine, me not liking it doesn't mean it's wrong.
They will continue the ‘buy-a-box’ promo going forward.
Walkers from the Chinese set.
I’m fine w the buy a box thing but I get people not liking it
Kind of sucks that you can’t have pir or toothy as the General of your deck and still include the other
They could easily say partner is part of the color identity. Activated ability are already a presidence for that
I’m not sure how that’s how it works…the RC may allow it if you include both in the Command Zone.
The rules are written so it’s still Partner. It just has additional tutor rules.
It’s not how it works now but it’s an easy rules change
The reminder text just mentions the tutor bit.

"Though not in the reminder text of the mechanic, the legendary "partner with" cards that reference each other can, together, be your commanders in the Commander format! We were looking for ways to make these creatures both able to be your commander, and a variant on partner made a ton of sense. They do need to be paired up with each other (for example, Toothy and Pir can be played together; Toothy and Ravos, Soultender can't), and we were able to make some really exciting pairs this way."
Just say if a card his partner with the partner card is part of the color identity
It isn’t partner, because you can’t partner them with other previous partners
However it gets done I guarantee it gets done. There’s no way the RC saw these and just said “ah well, guess they won’t work in Commander”.
I wrote “partner with”
They’ll make them legal for 4 weeks in Uncommander
Just for <@U4V5EHQ2G>
Walkers fee pretty intro deck in power, though maybe that’s the intent

Notable enchantments that aren’t Quests/Sagas that work with Pir and Toothy:
As Foretold
Druids Repository
Mind Unbound
Gutter Grime
Legacy’s Allure
Midsummer Revel
Rereading the announcement both can be in the command zone; I just wish they’d said it explicitly vs. obtusely.
It was necessary for the cards or otherwise the reminder text would take up too much of the card
I don’t mean on the reminder text - I meant in the article.

Also, more notes on the "Partners with" cards:
they appear at uncommon and above.
there are 11 pairs in the set
if one appears in a booster, they both appear in the booster
They did say it explicitly.

They said they could be commanders…I know people. That little bit of interpretation will lead to some confusion. It’s silly, I know, but it would be better if they explicitly said they can both start in the command zone. Yes, I’m being pedantic. Yes, it’s stupid, but always remember my creed: “People, are the worst.”
Henry, it's not one deck, it's three decks.
Pir, Toothy and Pir & Toothy
Sure
Three variations on one deck

I know what it says, <@U3FV90TCZ>. I’m telling you…mark my words. There will be questions.
I have every faith in people.
I think they're three very different decks
They are all counters decks.
If you don’t use the partner, then they’re mono-colored versions.
both want to put counters on things. Where you put them may be different, but that’s a difference in flavor vs. actual deck construction.
I’m with Henry. It doesn’t say it on the card, which will confuse people
<@U3MTJRAQL> and I agree…we’re doomed.
Time to pack it in, we've had a good run.
Let me be Henry, and rant that Wizards once again can't make a non-value UG commander.
Not even a little bit.
I wasn’t even going to mention it.
10/15 UG commanders now draw cards or benefit from drawing cards.
Wait? How about we put counters on things, and then draw cards for the number of counters! They’ll never see it coming!
Oh, and you’ll notice it’s a leaves the battlefield trigger.
Wait what. Are you kidding me?
Missed that little nugget, eh? Because nothing bad can happen there.
Hello Master Biomancer... so dumb.
I'm much more of a fan of GW and GB based counters, so the fact that UG gets some of the strongest pay-offs bothers me
I’m telling you, WotC has painted themselves into a philosophical corner with certain color pairs. Simic benefits, while Boros langurs.
That...I...ok
Weird, but also they aren’t good, so.
0/2 for announcements today, IMO
Not sure what you mean there <@U3MTJRAQL>
I dislike the announcements
You don’t like Ravnica?
I like ravnica. I guess I don’t really view it as an announcement? We’ve known for the past year that’s where here going
No, we suspected it. We knew were were going back, we didn’t know it would be this fall.
In any case. If green has a Hardened Scales Commander, guaranteed Doubling Season is getting reprinted.
That would be quite nice
No chance. The general is a mini-doubling season vs. a hardened scales.
Pir references any type of permanent. That’s very specific language. It indicates that green is doing more than just +1/+1 counters in this set. That makes Doubling Season a cert
That’s my point. They won’t reprint it because it’s too strong.
It’s a supplemental set. Even in the original MM doubling season wasn’t too strong. The only place it breaks things is EDH
Which is a much larger market every year and here they provided generals that, once again, interact with planeswalkers. I don’t see it happening, especially for a $60 card.
I’m in a bettin mood if we wanna make it interesting :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye:

Joey, don't go 0-2 on your friendly wagers...

Berserk was like, $50+ for beat copies
Show was $40 or so
I’m in.

I wouldn't play Djeru if winning was all that important, but I can see how I close out games in that deck. Not sure how I would do it in Jhoira

He just does his durdle thing, then passes
Yup…so I love the “Oh! I don’t do that!” attitude.

Another problem with partners that doesn't really get talked about is there's a potential scaling issue there. If a lot of the partners aren't great then maybe the advantages of essentially starting the game with an extra recastable card effectively in hand isn't maybe a huge deal. The more that get introduced the more potential there is for potent combinations, and the combo being potent makes the extra card thing that much more powerful.
Sure - it guarantees they have to circumscribe them...except for the Simic ones.
And in a way that damage is already done
Any good partner they make gets better paired with the two simic ones
